      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "Even a single low dose of ibuprofen can be nephrotoxic and cause acute kidney injury in people with chronic kidney disease, regardless of whether their numbers were \"stable\" previously. NSAIDs reduce blood flow to the kidneys, and this effect can be sudden and severe even with minimal usage. Please do not take that pill and instead use safe alternatives like acetaminophen after confirming the dosage with your pharmacist.",
      "source": "target",
